    "body": "Ref: #38525\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nOur JSON-RPC client is oriented towards LSP implementation and contains logic for message framing. This belongs to the LSP extension beneath JSON-RPC, known as the [“base protocol\"](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#baseProtocol). This logic should be decoupled to improve clarity.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nExtract `vim._framer` for message framing. Since this function is used in the test suite, it may be beneficial as a standalone module; furthermore, perhaps it and `vim._transport` could also be used for `vim.net`? cc @yochem",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I hesitated for a long time on the interface design of this message framer, and this might not be its final state. However, in this PR, I have decoupled the message framing logic from RPC and ensured full compatibility, and this new module is private. I suppose we can leave it like this for now and make adjustments in #38525, or redesign it once we have other framing requirements.",
